body: "Research snapshot (2026-05-17):\n- Existing init flow lives in src/cli/commands/init.ts and already owns directory creation, settings writes, TTY-only wizard prompts, --defaults, --author, --with-packages, runtime schema scaffolding, package installation, and next_steps output.\n- Command wiring for init is in src/cli/register-setup.ts. Help examples/tips are in src/cli/help-content.ts. SDK/MCP action contracts expose init optional keys from src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts. JSON key-order regression for init is covered in tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts.\n- Settings schema/types currently have telemetry prompt state but no project-level agent-guidance state. Add a narrow settings.agent_guidance object for prompt completion, decline, template version, and last checked files. Unknown settings are stripped today, so schema/types/serialization must be updated together.\n- AGENTS.md exists in this repo and already contains extensive pm guidance; CLAUDE.md is absent. The feature should work generically for either root AGENTS.md, root CLAUDE.md, both, or neither.\n- Existing docs already define the content source: docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md, docs/COMMANDS.md, docs/QUICKSTART.md, and guide topic workflows. The init-injected block should be shorter than this repo AGENTS.md and idempotent, with stable markers and a template version.\n\nImplementation direction:\n1. Add an idempotent detector/patcher for AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md that checks for a stable pm guidance marker plus core command tokens such as pm init, pm context, pm search, pm create, pm claim, pm files/docs/test, pm test --run, pm close, pm release, and PM_AUTHOR.\n2. Extend pm init with explicit modes, preferably a single value flag such as --agent-guidance <ask|add|skip|status> plus a convenience alias if desired. Default ask mode should prompt only in TTY and only when guidance is missing and the project has not declined.\n3. On approval, append or create a clearly marked section without clobbering user content. On decline, write project settings so the user/agent is not asked again. A later pm init --agent-guidance add should override the decline and write the section.\n4. Non-interactive init should never block. It should report guidance_missing in next_steps/warnings unless --agent-guidance add/skip/status makes intent explicit.\n5. Update help, contracts, config/settings docs, tests, and plugin/guide surfaces so agents can discover the workflow."
